---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

/** Meaning / principle sections — aligned with Doctrine heading on sigil detail */
const hMeaning =
	'border-b border-neutral-800/35 pb-6 text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-amber-200/88 md:text-xl';
/** System role — aligned with Underlay heading on sigil detail */
const hSystem =
	'border-b border-neutral-800/35 pb-6 text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-cyan-300/82 md:text-xl';
const pBody = 'mt-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400';
---

<Layout title="What is a Sigil · Empyrria Sigil Codex" currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}>
	<main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12 md:px-8 md:py-16">
		<p class="text-[0.65rem] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-neutral-500">Codex</p>
		<h1
			class="mt-3 text-[2.125rem] font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 md:text-[2.75rem] md:leading-[1.08]"
		>
			What is a Sigil
		</h1>

		<div class="intro whitespace-pre-line mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-400 md:text-[1.0625rem]">
			{`A sigil is not decoration.
It is not a symbol added for style.
It is a form of meaning made visible.`}
		</div>

		<section class="mt-12 space-y-12 md:mt-14" aria-label="Article">
			<div>
				<h2 class={hMeaning}>Definition</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>
					Within Empyrria, a sigil is a symbolic codification of a system element: a doctrine, a state, a core of
					being, or a relation between entities.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
					It does not represent something loosely.<br />
					It defines it, stabilizes it, and allows it to be recognized.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hMeaning}>Function</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>
					A sigil always does something. It may align, stabilize, warn, connect, or activate.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
					It is not passive imagery. It is a functional element within a larger system.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>System Role</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>
					Sigils exist inside a structured architecture. Core defines identity. Doctrine defines direction. State
					defines alignment. Relation defines interaction. Command defines action.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hMeaning}>Design Principle</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>
					A sigil must be readable at a glance. Its structure must feel intentional. Every line, axis, and form must
					belong to the same internal logic.
				</p>
				<div
					class="mt-6 border-l border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10 px-4 py-4 text-sm italic leading-relaxed text-neutral-400 whitespace-pre-line"
				>
					{`Meaning comes before detail.
Clarity comes before decoration.`}
				</div>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hMeaning}>Presence</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>A strong sigil does not look created. It looks recognized.</p>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
					It carries weight. It holds position. It feels like it belongs to a system larger than itself.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<p class="mt-14 text-sm text-neutral-500 md:mt-16">More entries will be added as the system expands.</p>

		<nav class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-neutral-800/60 pt-10 text-sm" aria-label="Continue">
			<a
				href="/codex"
				class="text-neutral-400 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-neutral-500/40"
			>
				← Codex hub
			</a>
			<a
				href="/codex/system-architecture"
				class="text-neutral-400 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-cyan-300/85 hover:underline focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-cyan-500/30"
			>
				→ System Architecture
			</a>
			<a
				href="/showcase"
				class="text-neutral-400 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-neutral-500/40"
			>
				→ Showcase
			</a>
		</nav>
	</main>
</Layout>
